1 (1) review available wraparound services, which refers to stabilizing services as part of a
2 strengths-based planning process that occurs in a team setting to engage with children, youth, and their
3 families;
4 (2) review services that may be applied to any housing development for homeless individuals to
5 access safe, decent, and affordable housing; and
6 (3) review permanent supportive housing opportunities, which REFERS to permanent housing in
7 which housing assistance, such as long-term leasing or rental assistance, and supportive services are provided
8 to assist households with at least one member with a disability in achieving housing stability.
9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that, in relation to wraparound services and permanent supportive
10 housing, the committee examine the efficacy, cost savings and offsets related to HEALTH CARE and public safety
11 and consider state programs that may support these service models.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the committee examine all available homelessness data in
13 Montana, including data related to the last housed location of individuals seeking homeless services and where
14 rural individuals without stable housing may seek services or shelter. The committee shall make a good faith
15 effort to examine data or ANECDOTAL homelessness information from EACH county in Montana.
16 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the study include input from appropriate stakeholders, including but
17 not limited to homeless shelter directors and staff, homeless services providers, Montanans who have
18 experienced homelessness, homelessness experts and advocates, local governments, and appropriate state
19 department staff.
20 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that if the study is assigned to staff, any findings or conclusions be
21 presented to and reviewed by an appropriate committee designated by the Legislative Council.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that all aspects of the study, including presentation and review
23 requirements, be concluded prior to September 15, 2026.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the final results of the study, including any findings, conclusions,
25 comments, or recommendations of the appropriate committee, be reported to the 70th Legislature.
